**Method 1: Using the Right-Click Menu**

1. First, locate the text you wish to underline in your OneNote page.
2. Next, right-click on the selected text. This will open the context menu.
3. On the top of the screen, you will see a list of options. Look for the "Home" tab or the "Format" tab, depending on the version of OneNote you are using.
4. Click on the "B" button (bold) or the "U" button (underline) to underline the selected text.

**Method 2: Using the Highlight and Underline Tool**

1. First, locate the text you wish to underline in your OneNote page.
2. Select the text by highlighting it. You can do this by clicking and dragging your mouse over the text.
3. On the top of the screen, you will see a toolbar with various formatting options. Look for the "Home" tab or the "Format" tab, depending on the version of OneNote you are using.
4. Click on the "U" button (underline) to underline the selected text.

