In modern times, this tradition has been adopted by many cultures, and it is generally accepted that the left ring finger is the correct place to wear a wedding ring. This is because the left hand is often associated with the heart, and wearing the ring on this finger is a symbolic representation of the bond between two people.

Therefore, based on this reasoning, the correct way to show you're married with jewelry is to wear your wedding ring on your ring finger on your left hand.

