2. Once the grains are cooked, we melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a pan over medium heat.
3. We then sauté the cooked grains in the melted butter for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. This helps to infuse the grains with flavor and texture.
4. Next, we stir in 1/2 cup of chopped dates. The heat from the butter will help to soften the dates and bring out their natural sweetness.
5. We also add 1/2 cup of chopped mixed herbs, such as dill, tarragon, and/or parsley. These herbs will add a fresh and aromatic flavor to the dish.
